<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10028d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10028d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10028d"> 28(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ pillarbox ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Aujourd&apos;hui qu&apos;il suffit de jeter dans une bo&icirc;te aux lettres une carte postale, un pli quelconque, affranchi ou non, pour &ecirc;tre certain que la missive s&apos;en ira rapidement et s&ucirc;rement &agrave; sa destination &hellip; <font color="green">[Today, it&apos;s enough to toss a postcard or any kind of envelope into a letter-box, stamped or not, and one is certain that the missive will go quickly and reliably to its destination. ]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01009k" href="c01all.htm#c01009k">VI.C.01:009(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
